<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1923-04-06T16:32:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1923-04-06T16:32:00-05:00" n="287" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d287">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">824.51/175: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Bolivia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Cottrell</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">La
                                        Paz</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1923-04-06T17:00:00-04:32"><hi rend="italic">April 6,
                                        1923—5 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received 6:45
                            p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>20. Referring to the Department’s telegram of April 3, 1 p.m. Accompanied
                            by Secretary of Legation Flack had very agreeable conference with the
                            President this afternoon setting forth points in Department’s telegram.
                            President said he had contract and all facts before him and knew the
                            situation and was glad to have the views of the bankers.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Cottrell</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>